title: The Twenty/Twelve Anthology
description:
Thanks to all the artists that contributed to the cause, Twenty/Twelve was larger than life and it was because of you that I tried to handle the 70+ artists alone. I believed in a lot of you, Some before they were even "ready". Some of you have moved 
on to different sounds a few of you have moved onto major deals and signings or have traveled the world twice over. This is more than I could have ever hoped for from a roster. Thank you! Also to the fans of 20/twelve thank you for supporting the label with your positive responses to the music we released in just a short time. This one is for you!


We were the early adopters of of the sound, The purveyors. We were a legion, A Netlabel army.

May this catalog be shared forever.


* The Twenty/Twelve Imprint was a Neltabel that rose to fame in 2009 being the first ever Dubstep netlabel catering to the creative commons license and was also a nominee for "Best New Label" in 2009 for the Dubstepforum Awards without having a single commercial release. In was placed on indefinite hiatus in 2010. This is it's legacy.
